    <span style="font-family: Arial;"> </span>
    <p><i><span style="font-family: Arial;">Hello!</span></i></p>
    <p><span style="font-family: Arial;"> I'm Hengrui Luo (Henry).<br>
        Currently, I am a Ph.D. student in the Department of Statistics, The
        Ohio State University at Columbus. <br>
        Here is my <a href="https://henrylaw.weebly.com/uploads/2/3/7/6/23762948/cv20191212.pdf">curriculum
          vitae</a>. <br>
        =====<br>
        My research interests include<br>
      </span> <span style="font-family: Arial;"><b><u><i>(A) Topological Data
              Analysis (TDA) </i></u></b><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I work on detection and inference of low dimensional
        topological/geometrical features of datasets.<br>
      </span> <span style="font-family: Arial;"><b><u><i>(B) Bayesian methods </i></u></b><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I work on non-parametric methodology and effective
        scalable modeling of large-scale datasets. <br>
      </span> <span style="font-family: Arial;"><b><u><i>(C)High dimensional
              probability</i></u></b><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I am particularly interested in the application of
        recovering signals from multi-scale noisy inputs. <br>
      </span> </p>
    <span style="font-family: Arial;"> </span>
    <p><span style="font-family: Arial;">Interestingly (and also
        coincidentally), all my research is more-or-less related to scaling or
        partition of certain spaces.<br>
        =====</span></p>
